analysis.title: Global Market Outlook
analysis.content: NEUTRAL REGIME PERSISTS AMID VOLATILITY EXPANSION. The GMS 52 print signifies a precarious equilibrium within Phase 2 weights, characterized by a lack of liquidity convexity. While high-yield credit spread compression persists, the VIX elevation above 20 indicates systematic regime degradation. The cooling fiscal-monetary nexus and negative equity momentum dictate a tactical retreat until volatility subsides and liquidity re-accelerates into the risk-asset matrix. [ACTION: WAIT FOR PULLBACK]
